<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/8–2444:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-24T19:00:00+01:00">August 24,
                                    1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3284. Legation’s 3270, August 24, 3 p.m. Madame Kollontay has just
                            advised me that she saw Foreign Minister Günther this afternoon and
                            fully supported our <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi>. She described Mr.
                            Günther’s reaction as “not unfavorable”.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>